task.summary:
Fixes MRO issues with class hierarchy.
I got an inconsistent MRO error when I went to define the SettableIngredient. I had to change the order of parent class declarations in HasName, to resolve the problem.

Updates the Ingredient class to rely on a data src callback
Previously, the ingredient class took the unique name or the datafile name, and used it to look data up from the database. That approach smells bad - the model shouldn't know about the persistence module.

Drafts in the constructor for SettableIngredient.
Adds tests to validate the constructor can create a new instance, and load data if provided.

Tidies up the current model classes.
Adds some comments to the existing classes, and splits some of the various classes in model.main out into their own files.

Refactors QuantityOf._validate_pref_units into standalone function.
Updates QuantityOf._validate_pref_units to be less mixed up. This commit moves it out into its own function, which can then be used in a truly local sense by the QuantityOf class, while perserving its flexibility and reusablity as a module function.

Refactors classes using src data to use an intermediary base class.
Fixes the complexity caused by the current pattern, where the writeable classes have to try and pump their local data through a source function to extend from the readonly classes. This design pattern affected both NutrientRatio and QuantityOf. This commit updates both of these classes and their respective tests. This commit also fixes some of the legacy function in the nutrient module test suite.

Adds check for mandatory names on nutrient config validation.
Adds a check to ensure that any nutrient names listed in mandatory nutrient names are also primary names.

[06A22] Tests functionality on IngredientBase.
Updates the tests to isolate functionality on the IngredientBase class.
Resolves bug [DEABE], where SettableIngredient would allow an ingredient name to be duplicated.
Resolves [75ABB], SettableIngredient.name cannot be set to None.

[E2050] Fixes the bug causing an exception if cost's load method is called without cost data in the dict.
Also adds a number of tests to the SettableIngredient test suite.
[2A433] Fixes the bug causing `HasSettableName.load_data` to raise an exception if there is no name key in the data dictionary.

[96A4B] Adds `HasFlags.flag_is_defined()` method, to determine if a named flag is defined on an instance.
Also adds basic integration tests for HasSettableFlags on SettableIngredient class.
[EEA41] Completes addition of simple integration tests for SettableIngredient.
[EEA41] Completes addition of simple integration tests for SettableIngredient.
[1EA06] Adds basic implementation & tests for IngredientAmount class.
[6BBD4] Fixes the factor 100 scale error with the nutrient quantities in the database.

Introduces caloric functionality into the model.
Brings in a new functionality class - HasNutrientMasses, and with it, methods to query the mass of a named nutrient on anything that implements HasNutrientMasses, and also a property to query the number of calories on anything that implements HasNutrientMasses. Also updates HasNutrientRatios with an additional property to return the calories per gram.

[29D43] Adds basic implementation for `SettableIngredientQuantity` class.
Makes a few changes to HasNutrientMasses class, so that the SettableIngredientQuantity class uses the SettableQuantityOf base.
[1A429] Refactors the quantity module data types into their own file.

Implements the start of an experimental investigation into changing the QuantityOf class to actually inherit from the class it is quantifying.
This turned out to not work nicely, because we need to be able to describe quantities of global instances, which we don't want to keep instantiating. Instead, we want to be able to pass a reference to the global instance into the instance modelling a quantity of it.
[B9DEE] Adds implementations for the `BaseRatioOf` class.
[6995A] Removes the ambiguous `IsDefined` class.
[4A892] Moves all of the model data-types into their own dedicated classes.
[2A2A7] Improves the naming conventions for the readable/writable/abstract/instantiatable classes.

[BDD72] Improves the naming conventions on the `QuantityOf` modules.
I started to realise that we needed both an abstract `HasReadableX` class as well as a concrete `HasReadonlyX` class. The former would be used when building other classes, the latter when instantiating readonly qty instances of another object on the fly.
[BDD72] Further improves the naming conventions on the `QuantityOf` modules.
[75167] Refactors the ratio functionality from `ReadableNutrientRatio` to `RatioOf` class.
[27142] Implements first passing test on IngredientRatioBase.

[D3743] - Some refactoring/renaming around ratio class.
All tests still passing.

#PD-1 Updates `QuantityRatio` to accept QuantityOf instances in constructor.
- Adds example to docstring for `IsQuantityOfBase.qty_pref_unit`. - Adds examples to docstrings for various `IsQuantityRatioOf` properties.
#PD-13 Very nearly fixes all tests after installing the `QuantityRatioOf` classes throughout. Only 14 tests failing now.
#PD-13 Completes installation of `IsQuantityRatio` classes. All tests passing.
#PD-6 Adds basic test coverage for `ReadonlyNutrientMass`.
#PD-14 Add tests to ensure we can't instantiate an `IngredientQuantity` (readonly or settable) with a `SettableIngredient` instance.

#PD-24 Implements the HasIngredientQuantitiesBase class.
- Also stubs in the first failing test for the RecipeBase class. This is the only failing test.
#PD-28 & #PD-29 Adds basic functionality associated with adding ingredient amounts and serve times, and updates `SettableRecipe` to support them.
#PD-30 Adds basic implementation of `HasInstructionSrc` classes.
#PD-31 Adds basic implementation of `HasTags` functionality into the model.

#PD-32 Implements bug fixes and test coverage for `HasReadableIngredientQuantities`.
Previously, we were doubling up on the `lambda: ...`, so we were getting another function from the data src function.
#PD-16 Implements tests on `ReadonlyRecipe` up to the `serve_intervals_data` method.
#PD-16 Implements all initial tests on ReadonlyRecipe class.
#PD-17 Implements `SettableRecipe` tests up to the name property.
#PD-40 Implements `time.validate_time` function.
#PD-42 Implements `time_is_in_interval` function.
#PD-38 Implement `HasReadableServeIntervals` class.
#PD-39 Implement `HasSettableServeIntervals` class.
#PD-46 Implement `HasSettableInstructionSrc`.
#PD-48 Implement `HasSettableTags`.
